(c) Material Adverse Change Exemption. In the event that, subsequent to the signing and delivery of this Agreement, any of the following occurrences take place, such events shall not be deemed to constitute a material adverse change:

(i) Any alteration or emergence of a potential modification in the financial or operational condition of the Transaction Entities and their respective Subsidiaries, collectively viewed, that, as per the Agent's sole discretion, is not significant and does not render marketing the Offered Shares inadvisable;
(ii) Any adjustment in U.S. or global financial, political, or economic conditions or exchange rates or exchange controls, the impact of which, according to the Agent's judgment, does not render it impractical to market or enforce contracts for the sale of the Offered Shares, whether in the primary market or with regard to transactions in the secondary market;
(iii) Any temporary halt or substantial restriction on trading securities generally on the NYSE MKT, or any establishment of minimum or maximum prices for trading on such exchange;
(iv) Any interruption or significant constraint in trading of securities on any national securities exchange or in the over-the-counter market;
(v) Any banking moratorium announced by any U.S. federal or New York authorities;
(vi) Any major disruption of settlements, payment, or clearance services in the United States or any other country where such securities are listed; or
(vii) Any attack on, emergence or escalation of hostilities, act of terrorism involving the United States, declaration of war by Congress, or any other national or international crisis or emergency, provided that, according to the Agent's judgment, the effects of such event do not make it inadvisable or impractical to market the Offered Shares or to enforce contracts for their sale.

(i) Warranty Certificate by Company Officers. The Agent shall have received a statement, dated the Settlement Date, from the Chief Executive Officer and the Chief Accounting Officer of the Company, acting jointly as Principal Financial Officers, to the effect that:

  1. They have made reasonable inquiry into the matters referred to in the representations and warranties of the Transaction Entities in this Agreement and, to their knowledge, such representations and warranties were accurate as of the Settlement Date;

  2. Each of the Transaction Entities has fulfilled all obligations and met all conditions required by this Agreement prior to or on the Settlement Date;

  3. No stop order has been issued by the Commission regarding any Registration Statement, nor are they aware of any such proceedings being initiated or planned at the time of their statement;

  4. The applicable filing fee was paid for any 462(b) Registration Statement (if applicable), in accordance with the Rules and Regulations;

  5. Since the most recent financial statements in the Registration Statement, there has been no material or adverse change, development, or event affecting the condition (financial or otherwise), results of operations, earnings, business, properties, or prospects of the Transaction Entities and their respective Subsidiaries, unless such changes are disclosed in the Registration Statement, General Disclosure Package, or Prospectus, or are described in the officers' statement.

